719038f-a.title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.
719038f-a.text:
Colonial Park: A view of the new playground and wading pool being
constructed by the W. P. A. in the northern end of the Park. The
photographers vantage point is on a line with W. 153rd Street and
shows an elevated viaduct on what would be W. 155th Steeet.
March 16, 1936.
W. P. A. Photo
Federal Art Project

719039f-a.title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.
719039f-a.text:
Colonial Park: A view northward showing the new swimming pool under
construction by the W.P.A. On the right appears buildings that line the
east side of Bradhurst Ave., north from and including West 147th Street.
This view is taken from the southern extremity of the Park, near 146th
Street.
March 16, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

719041f-a.title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.
719041f-a.text:
Colonial Park: The new swimming pool under construction by the W.P.A.
This view is southward from a peint near West 147th Street and shows the
southern extremity of the Park. Across the background is West 145th
Street (southernmost edge) with buildings upon the south side of same,
between Bradhurst (left) and Edgecombe (right) Aves. These are numbered
3200 to 338 respectively.
March 16, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
